First Lady Michelle Obama will be hosting her signature College Signing Day event in New York City's Harlem Armory as part of her Reach Higher initiative. Over 4,000 students from New York high schools will be in attendance. The event aims to inspire young people to pursue higher education and is part of the First Lady's Better Make Room campaign, which celebrates education and provides resources for students. The event will feature various celebrities and will be hosted by MTV in conjunction with Viacom's Get Schooled initiative. This will be the third annual College Signing Day event hosted by the First Lady, with previous events held in Detroit, Michigan and San Antonio, Texas. The event will be open press, with limited space, and will be livestreamed on MTV's Facebook page.